# NOTE: unlike every other chart in this repo, we intentionally COMMIT the vendored upstream tarball
# (charts/cluster-0.8.0.tgz) — so there is deliberately NO `charts/*.tgz` ignore rule here.
#
# Why: this chart is a file:// dependency of workloads, and it in turn pins a REMOTE dependency
# (cnpg/cluster). ArgoCD's repo-server runs `helm dependency build` only at the top level, so it won't
# fetch this transitive remote dependency over the network at render time. Vendoring it in git is the
# reliable path (the file:// package carries it along). Refresh it with `helm dependency update` here and
# re-commit both Chart.lock and charts/cluster-0.8.0.tgz when bumping the pin in Chart.yaml.
#
# PATCHED tgz (not pristine upstream): the ObjectStore templates (backup-/recovery-objectstore.yaml) had
# `helm.sh/hook: pre-install,pre-upgrade,pre-rollback` stripped -> `argocd.argoproj.io/sync-wave: "-1"`.
# Under ArgoCD a helm hook = ephemeral PreSync resource, so the ObjectStore got deleted and WAL archiving
# broke. Re-apply this after any `helm dependency update` (repack WITHOUT AppleDouble: COPYFILE_DISABLE=1).
# See docs/13_backups.md.
